#If the bill was $150.00, split between 5 people, with 12% tip. 
#Each person should pay (150.00 / 5) * 1.12 = 33.6
#Format the result to 2 decimal places = 33.60
#Tip: There are 2 ways to round a number. You might have to do some Googling to solve this.ðŸ’ª
#HINT 1: https://www.google.com/search?q=how+to+round+number+to+2+decimal+places+python&oq=how+to+round+number+to+2+decimal
#HINT 2: https://www.kite.com/python/answers/how-to-limit-a-float-to-two-decimal-places-in-python
print("welcome to the tip Calculator")
total_bill = int(input("what was total bill: "))
tip = int(input("what %age of tip would you like to give 10,12 or 15: "))
total_tip = total_bill + ((total_bill * tip) / 100)
total_people = int(input("how many people to split the bill? "))
calculator = (total_tip) / total_people
print(round(calculator , 2))
